  "soap_summary": "27-year-old male with ~3 days of large-volume watery diarrhea (hourly while awake), intermittent central/lower abdominal cramping (~6/10 when present), nausea and vomiting (including vomiting after milk), subjective feeling of fever (not measured), and possibly reduced urine output. Patient has taken paracetamol occasionally. Physician's provisional diagnosis is gastroenteritis; recommended oral rehydration (Dioralyte OTC), maintain hydration, and paracetamol for fever/pain. Advised to call back if not settled in 48 hours or if signs of dehydration.",
